This paper discusses the performance analysis of a routing protocol in mobile ad hoc networks (MANET) and focuses on detecting and isolating misbehaving nodes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses security issues related to node misbehavior, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of reputation-based cooperation schemes and performance analysis could also fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of the proposed protocol on the overall network performance, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
